    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Chromatic Aberration Section -->
  <section class="section" id="chromatic">
    <h2>Chromatic Aberration</h2>
    <p>Subtle RGB splitting creates depth and a cinematic 3D feel. Used sparingly on key UI elements.</p>

    <div class="chromatic-intro">
      <div class="chromatic-theory">
        <h4>How It Works</h4>
        <p>Chromatic aberration simulates the optical phenomenon where different wavelengths of light refract differently through a lens. By offsetting red and cyan color channels, we create a subtle 3D depth effect.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Intensity Scale</h3>
    <div class="chromatic-scale">
      <div class="chromatic-sample subtle">
        <div class="chromatic-box">
          <span>Subtle</span>
        </div>
        <div class="chromatic-specs">
          <code>--effect-chromatic-offset-subtle: 1px</code>
          <span>Use: Ambient depth, backgrounds</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chromatic-sample normal">
        <div class="chromatic-box">
          <span>Normal</span>
        </div>
        <div class="chromatic-specs">
          <code>--effect-chromatic-offset-normal: 2px</code>
          <span>Use: Cards, buttons on hover</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chromatic-sample strong">
        <div class="chromatic-box">
          <span>Strong</span>
        </div>
        <div class="chromatic-specs">
          <code>--effect-chromatic-offset-strong: 4px</code>
          <span>Use: Hero elements, focus states</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Live Demo</h3>
    <div class="chromatic-demo-grid">
      <div class="chromatic-demo-card">
        <div class="chromatic-avatar-demo">
          <div class="avatar-with-chromatic"></div>
        </div>
        <h4>Avatar Depth</h4>
        <p>Adds presence to the AI avatar</p>
      </div>

      <div class="chromatic-demo-card">
        <div class="chromatic-text-demo">
          <span class="chromatic-heading">Ferni</span>
        </div>
        <h4>Text Treatment</h4>
        <p>Hero headings with depth</p>
      </div>

      <div class="chromatic-demo-card">
        <div class="chromatic-button-demo">
          <button class="chromatic-btn">Start Talking</button>
        </div>
        <h4>Button Hover</h4>
        <p>Hover to see effect</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>CSS Implementation</h3>
    <pre><code>/* Token Variables */
--effect-chromatic-red: #ff0000;
--effect-chromatic-red-tint: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.2);
--effect-chromatic-cyan: #00ffff;
--effect-chromatic-cyan-tint: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.2);
--effect-chromatic-offset-subtle: 1px;
--effect-chromatic-offset-normal: 2px;
--effect-chromatic-offset-strong: 4px;

/* Usage with box-shadow (most common) */
.chromatic-element {
  box-shadow:
    calc(var(--effect-chromatic-offset-normal) * -1) 0 0 var(--effect-chromatic-red-tint),
    var(--effect-chromatic-offset-normal) 0 0 var(--effect-chromatic-cyan-tint);
}

/* Usage with text-shadow */
.chromatic-text {
  text-shadow:
    calc(var(--effect-chromatic-offset-subtle) * -1) 0 0 var(--effect-chromatic-red-tint),
    var(--effect-chromatic-offset-subtle) 0 0 var(--effect-chromatic-cyan-tint);
}</code></pre>

    <h3>Guidelines</h3>
    <div class="chromatic-guidelines">
      <div class="guideline-card do">
        <h4>✓ Do</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Use on hero elements and focal points</li>
          <li>Apply on hover states for interactivity</li>
          <li>Combine with subtle (1px) for ambient depth</li>
          <li>Use tinted (20% opacity) colors</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="guideline-card dont">
        <h4>✗ Don't</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Apply to body text—readability suffers</li>
          <li>Overuse—should feel special, not everywhere</li>
          <li>Use strong (4px) on small elements</li>
          <li>Combine with other heavy effects</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

